<TEXTAREA NAME="ReplyMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">[QUOTE]Originally posted by KaiserSos:
[B]Hail,

1. If someone maliciously killed the merchant and you had forces there there is a 50-50 chance a GM would spawn him for you if petitioned. I say 50-50 because all their decisions are seat of the pants and it depends which GM is about

2. A true nightmare is camping Rage 72 hours and to have the servers repatched 6 times in 4 days so you have the joy of assembling sub 52 types over and over to keel Naggy, waste 30 hrs camping RAge until they repatch Naggy back to life.

3. Rage should spawn several times a week once Naggy dies. However common practice at Verrant is a weekly patch because there is always some [usually cleric] item they feel the need to nerf. They then do an emergency repatch within 48 hrs to correct the bugs their weekly nerf patch introduced. This is about 48 hrs into the typical clerics rage camp which puts him within 24 hrs of a raGE spawn. It has also happened during rage spawn several times. I think that rage spawn is actually a trigger for 'emergency patching' sometimes given the frequency of hearing... Servers coming down in 10 minutes please camp... just as rage spawns.

3. There is a rumor that the next patch will change rage spawn. Although it might change to a triggered spawn, given VI incompetence I am anticipating perhaps having to clear 2-3 planes of all mobs including the GODs to trigger the spawn or some such.... only to have an emergency patch 2 days later to NERF the epic perhaps have it cast minor heal or something along those lines  :(


KaiserSos
Povar Templar 57
[/B][/QUOTE]

